<b>What is Survey Builder?</b><br>
Survey builder is an internal company tool that lets you custom design surveys for any of your feedback needs. It lets you
phrase and input your own questions, make changes, add HTML tags and even test drive the survey before sending it out.
You get a custom product, save time and get it out the door quickly.<p>

<b>Before you make a survey</b>
<ol>
<li>Clearly define your objective. 
<li>Review previous surveys. Feel free to copy any ideas and questions you like. This may save you time and duplication
     of effort. 
<li>Draft your list of questions and welcome text for the recipient. 
<li>Identify your target recipients, e.g. 
<ul>
<li>Internal staff
<li>Member dealers
<li>Newsletter readers
<li>Past PR consumers
</ul>
<li>Identify how to prompt your customers. 
<li>Mass email to recipients (See Arash)
<li>Related links on workwork.com web site
<li>A senior executive must approve your survey and its target market before going live. 
<li>Learn how to use the survey builder. Follow all instructions carefully. 
<li>Now begin creating your survey using Custom Survey Builder 
<li>Once you've built the survey, notify IT department. IT will make the survey live internally or on the Internet, and
     send out emails to list of recipients.
</ol>
	 
	 
<b>Features</b><br>
Custom survey builder lets you:
<ul>
<li>Review previous surveys.
<li>Make questions easily. A few clicks and you’re done.
<li>View the page layout in HTML without writing HTML code.
<li>Test drive your survey to make sure it’s robust.
<li>View results in bar and pie graphs that are generated automatically.
<li>Track each respondent’s activity on the survey.
</ul>
